
-------------------------------------------
MCPYTHON MODDING
-------------------------------------------

You are free to mod mcpython, write mods for the modloader or rewrite script of the main part.
Please make shoure that if you rewrite an mod of minecraft that everything is OK.
Modding Interface:
  1.: creat an folder in mods/ named how your mod should named
  2.: creat an file main.py in these folder
  3.: write: import globals as G\nclass <mymod>(G.mod): [stuff around your mod, see ModLoader.py, class Mod]\n
             G.modloader.register(<mymod>)
  4.: add block & item classes etc.
  5.: have fun!

adding an Block:
  1.: creat an File
  2.: creat the texture files
  3.: creat another (an model file)
  2.: write: import globals as G\nclass <myblockname>(G.blockclass): [stuff around your block, see block/Block.py]\n
             G.blockhandler.register(<myblockname>)